      "updated": 1779376394276,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ng update\n\n19-20\n\n20 - 21\n\n19 - 20 - 21\n\n\nTrue statement for DECADES: Developers should write TONS of unit tests. They are fast, easy, etc.\n\nThis is because running more complex tests (integration (system)), (end-to-end (system-integration)) is EXPENSIVE,\nhard, costs a lot, etc.\n\nSo - wishful thinking - if the developers test all teh low level stuff \"super hard\", the rest should just work, right?\n- WRONG.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ng update\n\n19-20\n\n20 - 21\n\n19 - 20 - 21\n\n\nTrue statement for DECADES: Developers should write TONS of unit tests. They are fast, easy, etc.\n\nThis is because running more complex tests (integration (system)), (end-to-end (system-integration)) is EXPENSIVE,\nhard, costs a lot, etc.\n\nSo - wishful thinking - if the developers test all teh low level stuff \"super hard\", the rest should just work, right?\n- WRONG.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
